-- Billionaire Premji Completes Transfer of Wipro Shares to Charitable Trust
-- B y   K e t a k i   G o k h a l e
-- 2010-12-10T06:48:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-10/billionaire-premji-completes-transfer-of-wipro-shares-to-charitable-trust.html
Azim Premji , the billionaire
chairman of Wipro Ltd., completed a transfer of 213 million
shares in India’s third-largest software exporter to a
philanthropic trust, the company said.  The shares, which constitute 8.7 percent of the company,
were transferred to the Azim Premji Trustee Co., according to a
filing to the National Stock Exchange today. The stake is valued
at 93.1 billion rupees ($2 billion) at yesterday’s closing price.  Premji, 65, who was ranked the third-richest Indian with a
net worth of $17.6 billion by Forbes India in September, had
pledged to transfer the Wipro shares to an “irrevocable trust”
and use the dividends to fund charity work in the country,
according to a Dec. 1 statement.  Wipro paid a dividend of 3.60 rupees a share this year and
may pay 4 rupees apiece for the year ending March 31, according
to  Bloomberg Dividend Forecast .  Wipro’s shares rose 1.4 percent to 443 rupees as of 11:37
a.m. in Mumbai.  To contact the reporter on this story:
